Count simple pseudo-classes in selector specificity
==================================================

LIB:     lexbor
TAG:     2.4.0
APPLY:   patch -p1 < this/file
TARGET:  source/lexbor/css/selectors/state.c

Bug
---
Lexbor v2.4.0 parses simple pseudo-classes such as `:hover`,
`:active`, `:focus`, and `:first-child`, but does not increment the
selector-list `b` specificity bucket for them. As a result, selectors
like `.btn`, `.btn:focus`, and `.btn:first-child` all report the same
specificity even though CSS treats pseudo-classes like classes.

Trigger
-------
Parse a stylesheet containing:

    .btn {}
    .btn:focus {}
    .btn:first-child {}

All three selector lists report the same specificity (`b == 1`) in
v2.4.0. Browser cascade semantics require `b == 2` for the latter two.

Fix
---
After accepting a supported simple pseudo-class, increment the `b`
specificity bucket through Lexbor's existing helper.

When upstream lands the fix
---------------------------
Delete this patch file. `scripts/fetch_deps.sh` will no longer
re-apply it on the next dependency refresh.

---
diff -u a/source/lexbor/css/selectors/state.c b/source/lexbor/css/selectors/state.c
--- a/source/lexbor/css/selectors/state.c
+++ b/source/lexbor/css/selectors/state.c
@@ -1495,6 +1495,8 @@
     selector->u.pseudo.type = pseudo->id;
     selector->u.pseudo.data = NULL;

+    lxb_css_selectors_state_specificity_set_b(selectors);
+
     lxb_css_syntax_parser_consume(parser);

     return LXB_STATUS_OK;
